        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-17T21:43:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "A lot of these return a zx_status_t that you should at least be ZX_CHECKing or ASSERT_NEing, but you’ve only ZX_CHECKed the launchpad_go().\n\n(Learnin’ based on my exploratory work at https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/crashpad/crashpad/+/820532/4/test/fuchsia/run_and_log.cc#226, which isn’t ready for anything yet.)",
      "revId": "2cf28382bc56edde002ebb1dc898e25374647a89",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "29d4cdc0_de364648",
        "filename": "test/multiprocess_exec_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-17T22:03:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Based on my reading of the docs, the intended use is that you don\u0027t error check all the way down, but instead only check at launchpad_go(), at it calls _destroy() whether in an error state or a successful launch.\n\nSo, if lp enters an error condition, it stays that way until destruction, and reports the first error when _go() is called and fails.",
      "parentUuid": "4392b008_b4f06592",
      "revId": "2cf28382bc56edde002ebb1dc898e25374647a89",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "50b0271f_6fcedb8e",
        "filename": "test/multiprocess_exec_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-17T23:29:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Based on my reading of the docs, the intended use is that you don\u0027t error check all the way down, but instead only check at launchpad_go(), at it calls _destroy() whether in an error state or a successful launch.\n\nWell, the existence of those zx_status_t return types gave me pause.\n\nLooking again at launchpad.h and launchpad.c, I see what you mean, in the form of lp-\u003eerror and lp_error(). And waiting for launchpad_go() with its easy errmsg out-param means that you get something a little more descriptive from the internals, at the expense of not knowing which of your launchpad_add_pipe()s is blameworthy.\n\nI usually like to trap failures as soon as possible, particularly in tests, but I guess this is OK.",
      "parentUuid": "29d4cdc0_de364648",
      "revId": "2cf28382bc56edde002ebb1dc898e25374647a89",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b5cad373_7b4ffe1c",
        "filename": "test/multiprocess_exec_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-17T23:39:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, the return values do make usage less clear. It does cut down on the verbosity a lot to only check at the end, at the expense of diagnosing the problem a bit later as you say.\n\nI guess a better framing is that error checking for each call is optional. I suppose the first thing we\u0027ll do if it ever fails in here is add all those checks though.",
      "parentUuid": "50b0271f_6fcedb8e",
      "revId": "2cf28382bc56edde002ebb1dc898e25374647a89",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e8432d68_b4ae9c0e",
        "filename": "test/multiprocess_exec_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 135,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-17T21:43:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do you want to launchpad_clone() anything here?\n\nThe only thing you definitely don’t want is LP_CLONE_FDIO_ALL.\n\nI don’t know how LP_CLONE_FDIO_STDIO behaves in conjunction with launchpad_add_pipe() that replaces stdin and stdout. It might be fine and would be an easy way to bring stderr into the child. Otherwise, please arrange to bring stderr to the child yourself, otherwise we’ll lose children’s useful diagnostics.\n\nYou definitely do want LP_CLONE_ENVIRON, almost certainly want LP_CLONE_FDIO_NAMESPACE, and based on my understanding, probably want LP_CLONE_DEFAULT_JOB too.",
      "revId": "2cf28382bc56edde002ebb1dc898e25374647a89",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ed4ffe6a_6f3ff9d1",
        "filename": "test/multiprocess_exec_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 135,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-17T22:03:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Seems reasonable.\n\nEven from looking at the code, I\u0027m not certain what happens if you first clone FDIO_STDIO and then replace some, so I went with clone_fd of STDERR.",
      "parentUuid": "e8432d68_b4ae9c0e",
      "revId": "2cf28382bc56edde002ebb1dc898e25374647a89",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
